(thirdQuint)Brain Study of Patients With Frontal Lobe Dementia and Parkinsonian Disorders.

 Objective To continue the cross-sectional and longitudinal studies performed by the Cognitive Neuroscience Section of NINDS on the neuroanatomy, cerebral metabolism, neuropsychology, and genetics of frontotemporal dementia, corticobasal syndrome, and related brain disorders.

 Study population Frontal lobe dementias and atypical basal ganglia disorders including frontotemporal dementia, corticobasal syndrome, and related brain disorders.

 Design A cross-sectional assessment of neuropsychological, brain anatomical and metabolic function, and genetic measures in subjects with these disorders.

 Outcome measures MRI, FDG-PET, neuropsychological and clinical tests, genetics, and neuropathology.

